================================================================================
  SECURITY COVERAGE
================================================================================

1. RBAC (Role-Based Access Control)
   - 3 ServiceAccounts (operator, driver, executor)
   - 6 Roles + 1 ClusterRole
   - 7 Bindings
   - Least privilege principle
   - No cluster-admin privileges

2. Pod Security
   - Pod Security Standards: restricted
   - Non-root user (UID 185)
   - Read-only root filesystem
   - All capabilities dropped
   - ResourceQuota + LimitRange

3. Secret Management
   - Kubernetes Secrets
   - External Secrets Operator (AWS Secrets Manager)
   - HashiCorp Vault integration
   - Sealed Secrets (GitOps)
   - 90-day rotation policy

4. Network Security
   - Default deny-all NetworkPolicy
   - Zero-trust networking
   - Egress control (S3, DB, Kafka)
   - AWS metadata service blocked
   - IP whitelisting

5. TLS/SSL Encryption
   - TLS 1.3 protocol
   - Strong ciphers (AES-256-GCM)
   - Mutual TLS (mTLS)
   - cert-manager integration
   - Auto-renewal

6. Audit & Compliance
   - API server audit logging
   - Fluentd log collection
   - Elasticsearch (1 year)
   - S3 Glacier (7 years)
   - Prometheus alerts

